  \end {tikzcd}


 between l\in  L and r\in  R admits a solution. We write L\rightthreetimes  R.

A weak factorization system in a category C consists of two classes of maps L and R so that:
every map admits an (L, R)-factorization;
L is the weakly left orthgonal class {}^\rightthreetimes R and similarly R is L^\rightthreetimes .

A lifting problem between maps l and r in a category C is a commutative square





